The first article "I Tried A Korean Skin Care Routine For A Month And This Is What Happened": its talk about a young lady she tried a Korean beauty products for a short time and in every week she took a pictures of her face to show if there are a changes after using the product. The tone of this article is formal because there was a use to words like: "what's up y'all" and the article is directed toward young people who are interested in K-beauty products. The second article "K-beauty: The rise of Korean make-up in the West": this article is talk about how the korean makeup became a famous and trend. The tone in this article is formal because there are no informal words and the audience of this article is general public and it is written by simple words.
So, there are differences between the two articles by the audience and the tone as mentioned above.